# PACE references (required)

Before writing "paragraph X.X says…" or "section N of PACE":

1. Check [PACE Code C 2023 (accessible)](https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pace-code-c-2023/pace-code-c-2023-accessible) or [legislation.gov.uk PACE 1984](https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/1984/60/contents).
2. Use consistent format: `PACE section 58` or `Code C paragraph 11.1A`.
3. Add the reference to `data/pace-reference-registry.json` if introducing a new citation used on the site.
4. Link Sources to the matching official URL.

## Common mistakes to avoid

- **s.58**: right to free legal advice — not a rule about court assessing "weight of evidence".
- **s.76/s.78**: exclusion powers — not automatic for every Code breach.
- **11.1A**: disclosure to enable legal advice — not full prosecution case disclosure.
- **Annex G / 12.3**: fitness to be interviewed — not the same as fitness to plead (CPIA 1964 s.4).

## Registry

Curated verified summaries live in `data/pace-reference-registry.json`. Run `npm run audit:legal` before commit.
